  "text": "SASL mechanism configuration validation in Apache Kafka at broker startup occurs through a multi-layer validation chain:\n\n1. **KafkaConfig.scala (lines 627-629)**: The broker configuration validator checks that sasl.mechanism.inter.broker.protocol is included in the sasl.enabled.mechanisms configuration when SASL is used for inter-broker communication. This validates the inter-broker communication mechanism against configured enabled mechanisms.\n\n2. **ChannelBuilders.java (lines 137-140)**: When creating SASL channel builders at broker startup, the enabled SASL mechanisms are retrieved from BrokerSecurityConfigs.SASL_ENABLED_MECHANISMS_CONFIG and for each mechanism, a JaasContext is loaded, which validates JAAS configuration presence.\n\n3. **JaasContext.java (lines 65-104)**: The loadServerContext method validates:\n   - Listener name and mechanism are provided (lines 66-69)\n   - JAAS configuration exists and is properly formatted for the mechanism (lines 92-98)\n   - JAAS configuration contains exactly one login module entry (line 97)\n   - Login modules are allowed by security policy (lines 106-115)\n   - Default JAAS configuration entries exist in system config if dynamic config not provided (lines 145-151)\n\n4. **SaslChannelBuilder.java (lines 141-186)**: During configuration:\n   - For each enabled mechanism, createServerCallbackHandlers (lines 317-336) creates mechanism-specific callback handlers:\n     * PLAIN -> PlainServerCallbackHandler\n     * SCRAM-SHA-256/SCRAM-SHA-512 -> ScramServerCallbackHandler (validates credential cache existence)\n     * OAUTHBEARER -> OAuthBearerUnsecuredValidatorCallbackHandler\n     * GSSAPI -> SaslServerCallbackHandler with KerberosLogin\n   - Each callback handler is configured with mechanism-specific JAAS entries (lines 149-151)\n   - Login managers and subjects are created for each mechanism (lines 166-176)\n   - For GSSAPI, native credentials are validated and added if available (lines 155-175)\n\n5. **SaslServerAuthenticator.java (lines 178-189)**: Constructor validates:\n   - sasl.enabled.mechanisms is not empty (line 179-180)\n   - For each enabled mechanism, a callback handler exists (line 183-184)\n   - For each enabled mechanism, a Subject exists (line 185-186)\n\n6. **OAuthBearerValidatorCallbackHandler.java (lines 106-129)**: For OAUTHBEARER mechanism, validates JWT validator configuration and JAAS config entries during configure callback.\n\nThe validation chain ensures that: (1) SASL mechanisms are enabled in broker configuration, (2) JAAS configuration exists and is properly formatted for each enabled mechanism, (3) mechanism-specific callback handlers can be instantiated, (4) subjects and credentials are available for authentication, and (5) mechanism-specific configuration (SCRAM credentials, GSSAPI principals, OAUTHBEARER JWT validators, etc.) is properly validated."
